, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Elton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Elton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of several places called Elton (Berkshire, Cheshire, Derbyshire, Durham, Herefordshire, Huntingdonshire, Lancashire, and Nottinghamshire). The Eltons in Chesire, Derbyshire, and Durham are from Old English <i>ǣl</i> ‘eel’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, settlement’. Elton in Berkshire is from the Old English female personal name <i>Æthelflǣd</i> (composed of the elements <i>æthel</i> ‘noble’ + <i>flǣd</i> ‘beauty’). Both Elton in Herefordshire and in Nottinghamshire are from the Old English personal name <i>Ella</i> + <i>tūn</i>. The Berkshire origin for the surname is especially well represented.","Norwegian: habitational name from a farm name in eastern Norway, in Old Norse <i>Elgjartún</i> ‘enclosed sacred place’ (or fenced in for <i>elg</i> ‘moose’?)."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant of   Dev ."],"variants":[{"name":"Deborah","meanings":["Biblical name (meaning ‘bee’ in Hebrew), borne by the nurse of Rebecca (Genesis 35:8) and by a woman judge and prophet (Judges 4–5) who led the Israelites to victory over the Canaanites. It has always been popular as a Jewish name. It was in use among Christians by the mid 16th century and was taken up by the Puritans in the 17th century, in part because the bee was a symbol of industriousness. Since then it has enjoyed enormous popularity, peaking in the 1960s. Among other famous bearers is the actress  Deborah Kerr  (  1921–2007 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas de Elton was born about 1182, in Elton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs Thomas de Elton."},"et":{"about 1182–":"umbes 1182–Surnud","1210–Female":"1210–Surnud","1240–Female":"1240–Surnud","1182–Male":"1182–Surnud","about 1182":"umbes 1182","1210":"1210","1240":"1240","1182":"1182","about 1240":"umbes 1240","Elton, Cheshire, England":"Elton, Cheshire, England","Elton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Elton, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1182–":"noin 1182–Kuollut","1210–Female":"1210–Kuollut","1240–Female":"1240–Kuollut","1182–Male":"1182–Kuollut","about 1182":"noin 1182","1210":"1210","1240":"1240","1182":"1182","about 1240":"noin 1240","Elton, Cheshire, England":"Elton, Cheshire, England","Elton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Elton, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1182–":"environ 1182–Décédé","1210–Female":"1210–Décédée","1240–Female":"1240–Décédée","1182–Male":"1182–Décédé","about 1182":"environ 1182","1210":"1210","1240":"1240","1182":"1182","about 1240":"environ 1240","Elton, Cheshire, England":"Elton, Cheshire, Angleterre","Elton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Elton, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Thomas d’Elton est né environ 1182, à Elton, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Mrs Thomas d’Elton."},"de":{"about 1182–":"um 1182–Verstorben","1210–Female":"1210–Verstorben","1240–Female":"1240–Verstorben","1182–Male":"1182–Verstorben","about 1182":"um 1182","1210":"1210","1240":"1240","1182":"1182","about 1240":"um 1240","Elton, Cheshire, England":"Elton, Cheshire, England","Elton, Cheshire, En